First of all I want to make some comments regarding your code:

 1. Follow Oracle convention and name classes in camel-case starting
    with capital letter. 
 2. Class name must not be plural: not `Doctors` but `Doctor`. In your case it describes single entity, not a group of doctors or something.
 3. Not necessary to name fields like `docid`, `id` is enough as it&#39;s defined in `Doctor` class. 
 4. Illness in my opinion must be separated class. Unfortunately, a patient can be ill more than once with different illnesses. 

